			<small class="commentmetadata"><a href="#comment-5374" title="">October 24th, 2008 at 5:35 pm</a> </small>

			<p>You can make the same thing with Betty Crocker brownie mix. Just leave out the water. I made dozens of these for Christmas last year. People just love them!</p>
<p><strong>Ah, but then you’re not using our super-duper King Arthur Flour! <img src="/blog/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley">  By the way, if you read that flour is “bleached,” do you know what that means? It means mill workers in hazard suits (that’s right – covered from head to toe) pour powdered bleach into your flour. I don’t know if Betty Crocker brownie mix uses bleached flour, but…. ewwwwww! if it does… PJH</strong></p>
 

		</li>

	
	
