			<small class="commentmetadata"><a href="#comment-64124" title="">December 11th, 2011 at 7:51 pm</a> </small>

			<p>Would it be possible to substitute ground flax seed &amp; water for the eggs in this recipe.  I have an allergy and a hatred for the taste of Ener-G.</p>
<p><strong>No guarantee, but try the following: Flax gel egg replacer – For 1 large egg, use 2 tablespoons flax meal (the more finely ground, the better) blended with 3 tablespoons cold water. Let for 10 minutes to thicken before blending into brownie batter. Good luck – PJH</strong></p>
 

		</li>

	
	
